We have been struggling with this bug for a while (see http://community.monogame.net/t/contents-of-rendertarget2d-gets-corrupted/1974). Now I managed to find the root of it. Here it is:

Create a rendertarget in LoadContent, and recreate it if ClientSizeChanged occurs. Also load a couple of textures.

``` C#
        protected override void LoadContent()
        {
            base.LoadContent();

            this.renderTarget = new RenderTarget2D(this.GraphicsDevice, this.GraphicsDevice.Viewport.Width, this.GraphicsDevice.Viewport.Height);
            this.Window.ClientSizeChanged += (sender, e) =>
                {
                    this.renderTarget.Dispose();
                    this.renderTarget = new RenderTarget2D(this.GraphicsDevice, this.GraphicsDevice.Viewport.Width, this.GraphicsDevice.Viewport.Height);
                };

            // Also load a couple of textures
        }
```

Comment out this line so orientation changes will trigger ClientSizeChanged :
https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/blob/893ee3522f67c6725f99ccf2bde5cf33b1276d10/MonoGame.Framework/Android/AndroidGameWindow.cs#L185
Or use builds prior to https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/pull/3560

Turn the screen of the phone on/off -> Rendertarget is sequentially created with already used ID
Rotate phone -> Rendertarget is sequentially created with new ID
